But I ſay, Nerves, Veins, Arteries and Skin are Diſſimilar Parts; for Galen, Hippoc. and Plat. Of the 
                           Ʋſe of the Parts, aſſert, that the Nerves are Marrowy within, Membrany without;

that the body of the Veins and Nerves are interwoven with Membranes, and ſeveral Fibres; and that the Skin conſiſts of Nerves, Veins and Arteries; and therefore they ought not to be numbred among the ſimilar Parts.
